k crossing it. Whatglorified the combination was a series of ember-bright cloudlets ridingalong, tattered and hooded, above the red sun which had assumed the shape ofa pawn or a baluster. "Look at the sabbath witches!" I was about to cry, butthen I saw Iris rise and heard her say: "That will do, Ives. Maurice hasnever met the person, it's all lost on him."

"Not at all," retorted her brother, "he will meet him in a minute andrecognize him (the verb was an artist's snarl), that's the point!"

